ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 3
 showed the FTIR spectra of aminosilica and GQDs bonded silica. The enhanced peaks at 3458cm−1 and 1630cm−1 symbolized the covalent attachment of GQDs to aminosilica. From the laser scanning confocal images (Fig. 4
) we could obviously see the fluorescence of GQDs bonded silica while aminosilica didn’t show this feature. This phenomenon further indicated the successful preparation of GQDs/SiO2 composite. Elemental analysis and specific surface area data of aminosilica and GQDs bonded silica were listed in Table S1. The increased carbon content and specific surface area again indicated the successful preparation of GQDs/SiO2 composite. According to Liang’s report [10], the specific surface area decreased after GO was coated on the surface of silica, because GO was so large that covered the pore of silica. However, the specific surface area of GQDs/SiO2 composite increased slightly, which indicated the pore-covering problem was avoided due to the small size of GQDs.
